WEBVTT

00:38.021 --> 00:40.455
It was a long time ago.

00:40.532 --> 00:43.467
Sometimes I can still
hear their voices

00:43.535 --> 00:44.969
across Sally's woods.

00:45.038 --> 00:48.701
There was Billy, Steve, Tommy,

00:48.775 --> 00:52.211
and the tall kid from
down the street... Joey.

00:52.278 --> 00:54.212
Yeah, it was Joey Walsh.

00:54.280 --> 00:56.715
My best friend was Timmy Burns

00:56.784 --> 00:59.514
who lived two blocks
away from me.

01:00.688 --> 01:03.657
We turned the woods
into a battlefield

01:03.724 --> 01:08.025
and dreamed that someday
we would become men.

01:15.871 --> 01:17.270
Did you hear it?

01:17.339 --> 01:19.137
What?

01:26.949 --> 01:29.440
Let's go, Timmy!
Let's go!

01:35.826 --> 01:37.726
Come on, Major!

01:42.232 --> 01:44.497
They've got to be
somewhere, Ronnie.

01:44.569 --> 01:46.059
Watch out.

01:46.171 --> 01:48.867
You've got to stay
in the ravine.

01:48.940 --> 01:49.998
Shh.

01:51.376 --> 01:52.934
Shh.

01:54.880 --> 01:56.711
Go! Go! Go!

01:56.782 --> 01:58.579
Look, there they are!

01:58.651 --> 02:00.448
Wipe them out!

02:00.519 --> 02:02.749
Aah!

02:02.821 --> 02:04.311
Aah!

02:04.390 --> 02:05.516
Aah!
Aah!

02:05.591 --> 02:07.287
Aah!

02:07.360 --> 02:09.122
Aah!
Aah!

02:09.196 --> 02:11.426
You're dead, and you know it!

02:11.531 --> 02:13.123
No, I'm not!

02:13.233 --> 02:14.996
Ronnie's dead!

02:15.101 --> 02:17.569
No, I'm not!
No, I'm not!

02:51.274 --> 02:52.969
Look at the mayor.

02:53.042 --> 02:55.603
I wonder where your mom is.

02:58.182 --> 03:00.173
Where is that woman?

03:00.251 --> 03:02.242
Hey!

03:03.821 --> 03:05.653
Hi.

03:11.763 --> 03:13.890
♪ 3 o'clock, 4 o'clock rock ♪

03:13.965 --> 03:15.125
♪ 5, 6, 7 o'clock ♪

03:15.200 --> 03:16.292
♪ 8 o'clock rock ♪

03:16.368 --> 03:18.803
♪ 9, 10, 11 o'clock,
12 o'clock rock ♪

03:18.904 --> 03:21.270
♪ We're gonna rock
around the clock tonight ♪

03:21.340 --> 03:22.568
♪ Put your glad rags on ♪

03:22.675 --> 03:23.972
♪ And join me, hon ♪

03:24.043 --> 03:26.375
♪ We'll have some fun
when the clock strikes 1:00 ♪

03:26.445 --> 03:29.711
♪ We're gonna rock around
the clock tonight ♪

03:29.783 --> 03:30.681
Donna!

03:30.751 --> 03:32.184
Donna, come back here!

03:32.252 --> 03:34.379
Get out of the way!

03:35.355 --> 03:38.119
Hey, you boys! Stop that!

03:38.191 --> 03:39.301
♪ When the band slows down ♪

03:39.326 --> 03:40.589
♪ We're gonna yell for more ♪

03:40.662 --> 03:42.338
♪ We're gonna rock around
the clock tonight # ♪

03:42.363 --> 03:44.263
Donna! Donna!

03:44.332 --> 03:47.062
Stevie Boyer
just gave Mary Barnett a ring.

03:47.135 --> 03:48.568
Can you believe it?

03:48.636 --> 03:50.103
Over there.

03:50.171 --> 03:51.103
O.K.

03:51.205 --> 03:52.696
Come here, come here.

03:52.808 --> 03:54.105
What is this?

03:54.209 --> 03:55.676
Is this a firecracker?

03:55.744 --> 03:56.711
What's wrong with you?

04:00.082 --> 04:01.640
Hey!

04:02.618 --> 04:04.712
Hey!

04:15.733 --> 04:17.166
This is boring.

04:17.233 --> 04:19.168
Yeah, square, man.

04:28.513 --> 04:31.004
Look, Daddy, the soldiers!

05:19.268 --> 05:21.293
Happy birthday, Ronnie Kovic.

05:21.370 --> 05:22.302
For me?

05:22.371 --> 05:23.804
Yes. Open it.

05:23.873 --> 05:25.306
That's really nice, Donna.

05:25.374 --> 05:26.808
Say thank you, Ronnie.

05:26.877 --> 05:29.937
Thanks, Donna, but
you didn't have to.

05:30.013 --> 05:31.708
Going to the woods tonight?

05:31.815 --> 05:33.214
They'll have fireworks there.

05:33.283 --> 05:35.251
Should be a real blast.

05:35.318 --> 05:36.216
Yeah, O.K.

05:36.286 --> 05:37.982
What is it?
Open it.

05:38.055 --> 05:39.613
Leave him alone.

05:40.725 --> 05:41.589
Beautiful.

05:41.659 --> 05:43.957
Hey, it's
the real thing, Ronnie.

05:44.028 --> 05:45.427
Feel that.

05:45.496 --> 05:47.259
Just like Mickey Mantle, Ronnie.

05:47.331 --> 05:49.766
Ain't he
a 4th of July firecracker

05:49.835 --> 05:51.234
in that hat?

05:51.303 --> 05:55.467
Yeah. He's my little
Yankee Doodle boy.

05:55.541 --> 05:58.408
Hey, get it!
Get it!

05:58.477 --> 06:00.001
Come on!

06:00.078 --> 06:01.842
Let's go!

06:30.445 --> 06:31.912
Did you like it?

06:31.980 --> 06:33.413
I don't know.

06:33.482 --> 06:34.915
I don't know.

06:34.983 --> 06:38.351
Hey, look how many
pushups I can do.

07:07.452 --> 07:09.249
Wow! Yeah!

07:09.320 --> 07:10.344
Yeah!

07:10.421 --> 07:12.754
Come on, Ronnie!

07:15.561 --> 07:18.029
Go, Ronnie, Go!

07:18.130 --> 07:20.564
Go, Ronnie!
You can do it!

07:20.633 --> 07:21.793
Go!

07:27.073 --> 07:30.440
Yes!

07:30.510 --> 07:34.173
Yes! That's my boy!

07:34.247 --> 07:36.113
That's my boy!

07:41.489 --> 07:43.320
Yes!

07:43.391 --> 07:47.351
Ronnie, you made it!

07:47.429 --> 07:50.592
Yeah, all right!

07:50.699 --> 07:54.328
Tommy! Ronnie!
Come on!

07:54.403 --> 07:56.564
You're going to miss it!

07:56.638 --> 07:58.869
Michelle! Barbara!

07:58.942 --> 08:00.603
You've got to see this!

08:00.677 --> 08:03.305
Not as a call to bear arms,

08:03.379 --> 08:04.812
though arms we need,

08:04.881 --> 08:07.543
but a call to bear the burden

08:07.617 --> 08:09.551
of a long twilight struggle,

08:09.619 --> 08:12.885
a struggle against
the common enemies of man...

08:12.957 --> 08:17.860
tyranny, poverty,
disease, and war itself.

08:17.928 --> 08:20.624
You'll get a licking
if you're late!

08:20.731 --> 08:23.360
In the long history
of the world,

08:23.468 --> 08:26.631
only a few generations
have been granted the role

08:26.705 --> 08:28.866
of defending freedom...

08:28.940 --> 08:30.339
Look, President Kennedy, Daddy.

08:30.408 --> 08:31.340
That's right.

08:31.409 --> 08:32.842
He's so handsome.

08:32.910 --> 08:35.607
I do not shrink
from this responsibility,

08:35.681 --> 08:37.910
I welcome it.

08:37.984 --> 08:41.943
Let the word go forth
from this time and place

08:42.020 --> 08:44.455
that the torch has been passed

08:44.523 --> 08:46.958
to a new generation of Americans

08:47.027 --> 08:50.190
born in this century.

08:50.263 --> 08:52.959
Let every nation know

08:53.066 --> 08:56.627
that we shall pay any price,

08:56.737 --> 08:59.070
bear any burden,

08:59.140 --> 09:03.804
support any friend,
oppose any foe

09:03.878 --> 09:05.869
to assure the survival

09:05.947 --> 09:07.744
and the success of liberty.

09:07.815 --> 09:10.785
I had a dream, Ronnie,
the other night,

09:10.853 --> 09:13.549
and you were speaking
to a large crowd

09:13.622 --> 09:15.283
just like him.

09:15.357 --> 09:16.756
Just like him.

09:16.825 --> 09:19.259
And you were saying
great things.

09:19.328 --> 09:21.229
And so, my fellow Americans,

09:21.297 --> 09:24.960
ask not what your country
can do for you,

09:25.068 --> 09:28.805
ask what you can do
for your country.

09:28.905 --> 09:31.135
Right! Right up!

09:31.207 --> 09:33.199
Get out!
Got to get out!

09:33.310 --> 09:34.709
You got to get out!

09:34.779 --> 09:36.212
You got to get out!

09:36.280 --> 09:38.805
Hit that switch!
Hit the switch!

09:41.152 --> 09:42.585
All right, hit the ropes!

09:42.653 --> 09:44.246
Go, go, go!

09:44.322 --> 09:45.880
Hand over hand over hand!

09:45.957 --> 09:47.857
Get those legs off those ropes!

09:47.926 --> 09:50.121
Come on, ladies,
let's come down!

09:50.195 --> 09:51.594
Let's come down!

09:51.663 --> 09:53.096
That rope is like life!

09:53.165 --> 09:55.690
You grab it
and hang onto it! Next!

09:55.767 --> 09:58.498
I want you to kill!

09:58.604 --> 09:59.696
You hear me?

09:59.806 --> 10:00.738
Yes, sir!

10:00.807 --> 10:01.739
Kill!

10:01.808 --> 10:03.241
I want that
conference championship!

10:03.309 --> 10:05.243
Do you want that conference
championship?

10:05.311 --> 10:06.300
Yes, sir!

10:06.412 --> 10:07.812
Get up! Heads!

10:07.881 --> 10:10.247
Get them up!
Do you hear me?

10:10.317 --> 10:13.650
Get your heads up, ladies!
Get your heads up!

10:13.721 --> 10:16.189
I want that
conference championship!

10:16.256 --> 10:19.225
If you want to win,
you got to suffer!

10:19.293 --> 10:21.228
You want to be the best?

10:21.296 --> 10:23.628
You got to pay the price
for victory,

10:23.698 --> 10:25.666
and the price is sacrifice!

10:25.734 --> 10:28.965
Susanne, no homework
at the table, please.

10:29.037 --> 10:31.028
No, Tommy.
After supper.

10:31.140 --> 10:32.004
Dad?

10:32.108 --> 10:33.006
Yeah?

10:33.109 --> 10:34.576
Can I come with you?

10:34.643 --> 10:36.543
There's the next
conference champion.

10:36.612 --> 10:38.079
Sorry I'm late, Ma.

10:38.147 --> 10:39.546
There's rice on the stove

10:39.615 --> 10:41.082
and fruit in the icebox.

10:41.150 --> 10:42.082
I can't.

10:42.151 --> 10:43.551
It's on your diet, right?

10:43.620 --> 10:46.555
I got to drop 3 pounds
by Saturday.

10:46.623 --> 10:48.557
Your brother's
a hard worker, Tommy,

10:48.625 --> 10:51.150
'cause he wants to be the best.

10:51.228 --> 10:53.992
Win or lose... in school,
in sports, in life...

10:54.064 --> 10:56.966
as long as you do your best,

10:57.034 --> 10:59.059
that's what matters to God.

10:59.137 --> 11:01.469
Win or lose, we still love him.

11:01.539 --> 11:03.473
Can I go to my room?

11:03.541 --> 11:04.473
Yeah, sure.

11:04.575 --> 11:06.476
Thank you, God, for this food.

11:06.545 --> 11:10.914
In the name of the Father,
the Son, the Holy Ghost, amen.

11:10.983 --> 11:12.746
Daddy, Jimmy took my doll!

11:12.818 --> 11:14.251
I'll get the doll.

11:14.319 --> 11:15.718
I hate his guts!

11:15.788 --> 11:17.221
Just go to bed.

11:17.289 --> 11:18.723
I didn't take anything!

11:18.792 --> 11:20.225
Where's your sister's doll?

11:20.293 --> 11:23.160
Jackie? Why
is Jackie not in bed?

11:23.229 --> 11:24.321
Ronnie.

11:26.599 --> 11:28.089
Where'd you get this?

11:28.168 --> 11:30.637
Why are you in my room?

11:30.704 --> 11:32.535
Don't change the subject.

11:32.606 --> 11:35.473
I don't allow Playboy magazine
in this house.

11:35.543 --> 11:36.510
Stevie gave it to me.

11:36.577 --> 11:38.477
You have filthy,
impure thoughts!

11:38.579 --> 11:40.046
God's going to punish you.

11:40.147 --> 11:43.083
I haven't even looked
at it yet, all right?

11:43.151 --> 11:46.587
Go to confession. I want you
to tell Father McKenna.

11:46.655 --> 11:49.055
I don't want to see
this filthy magazine

11:49.124 --> 11:50.557
in my house again.

11:50.625 --> 11:52.115
Now, take this away!

11:52.194 --> 11:53.628
What's going on?

11:53.696 --> 11:54.594
Nothing.

11:54.664 --> 11:56.097
What do you mean, nothing?

11:56.165 --> 11:57.996
Nothing, Dad. O.K.?

12:08.779 --> 12:11.839
You're out of bounds, guys.
Back inside.

12:11.949 --> 12:15.009
Come on, Kovic, back inside.
Come on, Kovic.

12:16.253 --> 12:18.586
Go, Ronnie.

12:18.656 --> 12:21.124
Kovic, back inside.
Come on, Kovic.

12:21.226 --> 12:22.591
Back inside.
Let's go.

12:22.660 --> 12:24.628
I want to see some explosion!

12:24.696 --> 12:26.129
Come on, Ronnie!

12:26.197 --> 12:27.858
No messing around!

12:27.932 --> 12:29.901
You're great, Ronnie!
You're great, Ronnie!

12:29.969 --> 12:31.368
Stay with him!

12:31.437 --> 12:33.371
Come on down!
All right!

12:33.439 --> 12:35.373
O.K. Get off
the mat.

12:35.441 --> 12:36.840
You're going to get...

12:39.278 --> 12:41.747
Get him! Get him!
Get him! Get him!

12:41.815 --> 12:43.407
Reversal.
2 points!

12:43.483 --> 12:45.644
All right!

12:45.752 --> 12:47.515
Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

12:47.621 --> 12:49.054
Ohh, you!

12:56.530 --> 12:58.623
One, red!
You're both up.

13:00.768 --> 13:03.328
All right, fresh start.
Fresh start.

13:03.404 --> 13:06.306
Stand up.
Don't let him get you!

13:06.375 --> 13:07.808
Don't let him get you!

13:07.876 --> 13:09.810
Pull him out!
All right!

13:09.878 --> 13:11.277
Watch those legs.
Watch him!

13:11.346 --> 13:14.076
Get him down!
Don't let him get the neck!

13:14.149 --> 13:15.742
No! No!

13:15.818 --> 13:17.376
No!

13:17.453 --> 13:19.580
You can beat him, Ronnie!

13:20.723 --> 13:22.782
Come on! Come on!
Come on!

13:22.892 --> 13:24.291
Ronnie, Ronnie, Ronnie!

13:26.896 --> 13:29.422
Bridge! Bridge!

13:29.500 --> 13:32.992
You can win!
Don't give up!

13:34.939 --> 13:36.668
Aah!

13:42.213 --> 13:45.080
Oh, no!

13:53.759 --> 13:55.317
O.K., son?

14:02.468 --> 14:03.936
Oh, no.

14:04.004 --> 14:06.063
Come on, get up.

14:11.111 --> 14:12.942
Attention!

14:13.013 --> 14:14.982
Forward march!

14:15.049 --> 14:17.244
Left, left.

14:17.318 --> 14:18.910
Left, right, left.

14:24.292 --> 14:26.056
Seats!

14:30.866 --> 14:32.493
Good morning.

14:32.601 --> 14:35.069
I am Gunnery Sergeant Hayes.

14:35.137 --> 14:36.570
This is Sergeant Bowers.

14:36.638 --> 14:40.473
United States Marine Recruiting Station,
Levittown, New York.

14:43.513 --> 14:45.071
We are here today

14:45.148 --> 14:48.242
at the request of your principal
Mr. Richards

14:48.318 --> 14:50.446
and other members of the faculty

14:50.521 --> 14:54.480
to tell you a little bit
about the Marine Corps.

14:54.558 --> 14:56.287
First off, young men,

14:56.360 --> 14:58.453
let's get one thing straight.

14:59.964 --> 15:03.924
Not everybody becomes
United States Marines.

15:04.036 --> 15:05.526
We want the best,

15:05.637 --> 15:08.071
and we'll accept nothing
but the best,

15:08.140 --> 15:10.108
because there
is nothing prouder,

15:10.175 --> 15:12.837
nothing finer, nothing
standing as straight

15:12.911 --> 15:15.881
as a United States Marine.

15:15.948 --> 15:18.007
Now, they've got the Army.

15:18.084 --> 15:20.052
They got the Navy.

15:20.119 --> 15:22.781
They got the Air Farce.

15:22.855 --> 15:25.324
And if you want to join them,

15:25.392 --> 15:26.791
be my guest.

15:26.860 --> 15:29.420
But if you want a challenge...

15:29.496 --> 15:32.693
if you want to try
something difficult...

15:32.800 --> 15:35.769
if you want to try to
achieve the impossible...

15:35.836 --> 15:38.738
you try 13 weeks of hell

15:38.807 --> 15:40.240
at Parris Island,
South Carolina,

15:40.308 --> 15:43.368
and you'll find out
if you got what it takes.

15:43.445 --> 15:46.778
You'll find out
if you really are a man,

15:46.848 --> 15:50.512
then the Marines may be
what you're looking for.

15:50.586 --> 15:51.951
Tarawa...

15:52.021 --> 15:53.249
Iwo Jima...

15:53.322 --> 15:55.847
Belleau Wood...

15:55.925 --> 15:58.257
the Frozen Chosan Reservoir.

16:00.030 --> 16:02.999
First to fight.
We have never lost a war.

16:03.066 --> 16:06.331
We have always come when
our country's called us.

16:06.436 --> 16:08.700
Now, Sergeant Bowers and I

16:08.805 --> 16:11.273
would like to open this up
to questions.

16:11.341 --> 16:14.743
So if any of you young men
do have questions,

16:14.812 --> 16:17.110
go ahead and raise your hands.

16:17.181 --> 16:19.115
Come on, now.
Don't be afraid.

16:19.183 --> 16:21.617
Don't forget, a good
Marine's a thinking Marine.

16:21.686 --> 16:23.051
Billy Vorsovich, sir.

16:23.121 --> 16:26.558
When would I get to wear
a uniform like you?

16:26.625 --> 16:29.395
You can be wearing this
in 13 weeks.

16:29.495 --> 16:30.962
Go! Go!

16:31.029 --> 16:32.724
Go, Massapequa!

16:32.798 --> 16:35.199
Go! Go! Go!

16:35.268 --> 16:37.065
Yay!
Yay!

16:40.840 --> 16:42.068
Hi, Donna.

16:44.611 --> 16:46.374
Go! Go!

16:46.446 --> 16:48.039
Go, Massapequa!

16:48.115 --> 16:49.309
Go!

16:49.383 --> 16:51.283
My brother's at school
at Adelphi.

16:51.352 --> 16:55.345
He said there will be a war in...
what is it?

16:55.456 --> 16:56.423
Vietnam.

16:56.490 --> 16:58.891
The Marines will be
the first in,

16:58.960 --> 17:00.928
and it won't last long.

17:01.029 --> 17:04.931
So if we don't sign up
soon, we'll miss it.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.434
I've already decided.
I'm going in.

17:07.502 --> 17:08.434
Really?

17:08.502 --> 17:09.935
Just like that?

17:10.005 --> 17:12.440
I'm not waiting.
I'm going in now.

17:12.508 --> 17:13.440
You're crazy.

17:13.509 --> 17:15.977
Our dads got to go to WWII.

17:16.045 --> 17:18.945
This is our chance
to be part of history.

17:19.015 --> 17:20.743
Yeah, just like our dads.

17:20.816 --> 17:22.682
Think about what you're doing.

17:24.087 --> 17:26.521
It could be dangerous
over there.

17:26.589 --> 17:28.615
You could get yourself killed.

17:28.692 --> 17:31.786
Where are you going,
squirrel head? College?

17:31.895 --> 17:34.228
I want to do something
with my life.

17:34.299 --> 17:36.699
I can get a degree in
Business Administration.

17:36.768 --> 17:38.963
You don't need
to serve your country?

17:39.037 --> 17:41.904
Don't you care
about anybody but yourself?

17:41.973 --> 17:43.406
Better dead than red.

17:43.474 --> 17:45.909
They got missiles pointed
at us everywhere. ICBMs.

17:45.978 --> 17:47.809
Coming in all around us.

17:47.880 --> 17:49.347
Cuba now.
90 miles away.

17:49.415 --> 17:50.814
They're taking over.

17:50.883 --> 17:52.214
When will we stop them?

17:52.284 --> 17:54.479
You can't stop them by yourself.

17:54.553 --> 17:56.418
Communism is
moving in everywhere.

17:56.488 --> 17:58.855
Where, Ronnie?
I don't see them.

17:58.925 --> 18:00.324
They're not here in Massapequa,

18:00.393 --> 18:02.793
so I'll just take care
of number one.

18:02.896 --> 18:04.864
That's right.
Me... Stevie, number one.

18:04.931 --> 18:07.866
Someone's got to stay
with the women and children

18:07.934 --> 18:10.335
while the men
go do the fighting.

18:10.404 --> 18:12.895
All I'm saying is,
think about it.

18:13.007 --> 18:14.440
Think about it, Ronnie.

18:14.508 --> 18:17.306
Stevie, who are you taking
to the prom?

18:17.378 --> 18:18.777
Wendy Daniels.

18:18.846 --> 18:19.778
Wendy Daniels?

18:19.847 --> 18:20.745
Wendy Daniels?

18:20.815 --> 18:22.545
He got desperate.

18:22.618 --> 18:25.086
Well, who are you taking,
Joey, your mother?

18:25.153 --> 18:29.089
Ronnie, who are you going
to take to the prom?

18:29.157 --> 18:30.590
You don't know her.

18:30.659 --> 18:32.628
She's a pretty girl
from Ronkonkoma.

18:32.695 --> 18:34.094
What's her name?

18:34.163 --> 18:35.357
You don't know her.

18:35.431 --> 18:37.331
What's her name, Ronnie?

18:37.433 --> 18:38.832
Her name is Lombardi.

18:38.901 --> 18:39.833
Lombardi?

18:39.902 --> 18:40.834
Yeah.

18:40.903 --> 18:42.495
Vince Lombardi?

18:42.605 --> 18:44.574
Rosanna Lombardi.

18:44.675 --> 18:46.609
She's from out of town, right?

18:46.677 --> 18:48.611
She going to get a motel?

18:48.679 --> 18:51.273
'Cause I'd like
to get in on that.

18:57.188 --> 19:00.157
Ronnie, would you take this
to section three?

19:00.225 --> 19:02.659
Check the stock for dog food.

19:02.727 --> 19:03.659
Dog food.

19:03.728 --> 19:05.696
Then finish
stacking the potatoes.

19:05.764 --> 19:07.163
Come on. Let's go.

19:07.232 --> 19:10.168
Let's do some work for a change.

19:10.269 --> 19:12.237
This goes in section three?

19:12.305 --> 19:13.237
Section three.

19:13.306 --> 19:14.500
O.K., Dad.

19:39.734 --> 19:41.497
Hey, Donna.

19:41.569 --> 19:42.661
Hi, Ronnie.

19:42.737 --> 19:43.534
Hi, Ronnie.

19:43.639 --> 19:44.264
Hi, Ronnie.

19:44.373 --> 19:46.432
How you doing?
How's...

19:46.542 --> 19:47.873
Good.

19:47.943 --> 19:51.379
I heard that you were going
into the Marines.

19:51.447 --> 19:52.675
Yeah, yeah.

19:52.748 --> 19:55.183
It's better than working at A&P.

19:55.251 --> 19:56.684
That's great, Ronnie.

19:56.753 --> 19:57.845
That's wonderful.

19:57.921 --> 19:59.855
I'm going to boot camp soon.

19:59.923 --> 20:01.857
I joined for four years,

20:01.925 --> 20:03.358
so I go to Vietnam,

20:03.426 --> 20:05.360
probably on the front line.

20:05.428 --> 20:06.554
Really?

20:06.630 --> 20:08.564
I'll see a lot of action.

20:08.632 --> 20:09.564
Wow.

20:09.633 --> 20:11.362
That's neat.

20:11.435 --> 20:13.869
Heard you got into that school.

20:13.938 --> 20:15.030
The letter?

20:15.106 --> 20:16.198
Yeah.

20:16.273 --> 20:17.763
Yeah, Syracuse.

20:17.842 --> 20:19.834
It's going to be really hard.

20:19.945 --> 20:23.381
Could I... Could I talk
to you in private?

20:23.448 --> 20:25.348
Oh, yeah. Sure.

20:29.121 --> 20:31.590
I've been meaning to call you.

20:31.657 --> 20:33.090
I was wondering,

20:33.159 --> 20:36.686
are you going with
someone to the prom?

20:36.763 --> 20:38.560
Yeah. I'm going
with Jed.

20:38.631 --> 20:40.098
Oh, yeah?
That's great.

20:40.166 --> 20:43.102
I mean, he's
a nice guy... Jed.

20:43.170 --> 20:44.603
Stevie Boyer told me

20:44.671 --> 20:48.038
that you were taking some girl
from Lake Ronkonkoma.

20:48.108 --> 20:49.541
Yeah. No, no.

20:49.610 --> 20:50.634
No?

20:50.744 --> 20:53.474
No. I don't have time
for that stuff.

20:53.581 --> 20:56.516
There's a lot of things
to take care of

20:56.584 --> 20:58.848
before you go in the Marines.

20:58.920 --> 21:01.548
I didn't even know
how much stuff.

21:01.623 --> 21:04.319
Maybe I'll see you
before I leave, O.K.?

21:04.392 --> 21:08.022
♪ Soldier boy ♪

21:08.097 --> 21:12.534
♪ Oh, my little soldier boy ♪

21:14.403 --> 21:22.403
♪ I'll be true to you ♪

21:22.646 --> 21:27.811
♪ You were my first love ♪

21:27.918 --> 21:32.720
♪ And you'll be my last love ♪

21:32.790 --> 21:37.659
♪ I will never make you blue ♪

21:37.728 --> 21:42.564
♪ I'll be true to you ♪

21:42.634 --> 21:47.503
♪ In this whole world ♪

21:47.573 --> 21:49.097
♪ You can love but one girl ♪

21:49.174 --> 21:51.108
I told you I love you.

21:51.176 --> 21:52.474
You promised.

21:52.545 --> 21:56.777
♪ Let me be that one girl ♪

21:56.883 --> 22:01.547
♪ For I'll be true to you # ♪

22:06.260 --> 22:08.728
The batter is Mickey Mantle.

22:08.796 --> 22:10.229
Mickey has two strikes

22:10.297 --> 22:12.697
and the chance
to put the Yankees

22:12.766 --> 22:14.199
ahead in this game.

22:14.268 --> 22:16.203
The pitcher gets his sign,

22:16.271 --> 22:18.705
takes his stretch,
checks the runners.

22:18.773 --> 22:20.240
Here's the pitch.

22:20.308 --> 22:22.139
Mickey swings, and he connects!

22:22.210 --> 22:25.145
There's a long drive
deep to center field!

22:25.213 --> 22:26.646
It is going, going!

22:26.715 --> 22:29.150
It is gone into the bleachers,

22:29.218 --> 22:31.482
455 feet away

22:31.587 --> 22:35.148
for Mickey's 491st home run!

22:35.258 --> 22:36.725
How about that?

22:36.792 --> 22:39.261
The crowd is on its feet,

22:39.329 --> 22:41.263
giving Mickey
a standing ovation.

22:41.331 --> 22:43.060
♪ And rattle your walls ♪

22:43.133 --> 22:48.196
♪ For the times,
they are a-changin' ♪

22:48.272 --> 22:50.832
♪ Come, senators
and congressmen ♪

22:50.908 --> 22:52.570
♪ Please heed the call ♪

22:52.644 --> 22:54.703
♪ Don't stand in the doorway ♪

22:54.779 --> 22:56.848
♪ Don't lock up the hall ♪

22:56.948 --> 22:59.246
♪ For the times,
they are a-changin' # ♪

22:59.317 --> 23:00.750
There's absolutely no question.

23:00.818 --> 23:02.217
The First Cavalry Division

23:02.287 --> 23:05.223
is the latest concept
in mobile warfare.

23:05.291 --> 23:06.724
One division is worth

23:06.792 --> 23:09.454
21/2 Russian
and 6 Chinese divisions.

23:09.528 --> 23:11.962
How well will
the individual soldier

23:12.031 --> 23:13.999
stand up here in Vietnam?

23:14.066 --> 23:17.798
What do you think,
Dad, about that?

23:17.904 --> 23:19.235
I don't know.

23:19.306 --> 23:20.773
13,000 miles...

23:20.874 --> 23:24.139
that's a long way to go
to fight a war.

23:24.210 --> 23:26.645
They fought the French
and the Japanese

23:26.714 --> 23:27.976
for 30 years.

23:28.049 --> 23:29.983
Can they be weeded out?

23:30.051 --> 23:32.019
Anything that lives in a cave

23:32.086 --> 23:33.485
can be weeded out.

23:33.554 --> 23:38.117
I just hope they send you
to Europe or Korea or...

23:38.193 --> 23:39.285
They can't.

23:39.361 --> 23:40.555
Someplace safe.

23:40.629 --> 23:43.564
Every Marine has
a tour of duty there.

23:43.632 --> 23:45.600
It's not like the Army.

23:45.667 --> 23:47.066
What's wrong with you?

23:47.135 --> 23:49.103
You served.
Uncle Bob served.

23:49.204 --> 23:50.900
I know, Ronnie.
I know.

23:51.007 --> 23:52.975
Remember what
President Kennedy said?

23:53.076 --> 23:54.941
There won't be
an America anymore

23:55.011 --> 23:57.411
unless people are willing
to sacrifice.

23:57.480 --> 23:58.879
I love my country.

23:58.948 --> 23:59.880
I know.

23:59.949 --> 24:01.416
And you're right, Ronnie.

24:01.485 --> 24:03.282
You're doing the right thing.

24:03.354 --> 24:05.151
Communism has to be stopped.

24:05.222 --> 24:07.520
It's God's will you go.

24:07.591 --> 24:09.149
We're proud of you.

24:09.226 --> 24:10.784
Be careful, that's all.

24:10.861 --> 24:12.624
Up there in Hanoi,

24:12.696 --> 24:15.632
they don't allow magazines,
newspapers, and televisions

24:15.700 --> 24:18.260
to cast doubts
on the military system.

24:18.336 --> 24:22.238
Don't you know what being a Marine
means to me, Dad?

24:22.340 --> 24:24.240
Ever since I was a kid,

24:24.309 --> 24:26.744
I've wanted to serve my country,

24:26.812 --> 24:28.245
And I want to go.

24:28.314 --> 24:30.248
I want to go to Vietnam,

24:30.316 --> 24:33.410
and I'll die there if I have to.

24:34.487 --> 24:37.457
The attitude of people
on the home front

24:37.524 --> 24:40.084
is very important in this war.

24:40.160 --> 24:43.095
Not a nice night for the prom.

24:43.163 --> 24:45.097
Can the South Vietnamese
government

24:45.165 --> 24:47.099
stand up to the North?

24:47.167 --> 24:48.601
We wouldn't be here

24:48.670 --> 24:50.228
if we didn't think so.

24:59.313 --> 25:01.680
Sometimes, God, I'm so confused.

25:04.653 --> 25:06.917
Sometimes I think I'd just...

25:07.990 --> 25:10.959
like to stay here in Massapequa

25:11.026 --> 25:12.756
and never leave...

25:15.198 --> 25:16.927
but I got to go.

25:21.805 --> 25:23.204
Just help me, Jesus.

25:23.273 --> 25:25.936
Help me to make
the right decision.

25:27.878 --> 25:29.641
Please, dear God.

25:56.542 --> 25:57.975
Ron.

25:58.044 --> 25:59.945
Ronnie, what happened to you?

26:00.013 --> 26:01.105
Ronnie.

26:16.431 --> 26:17.989
What...

26:18.066 --> 26:19.590
Oh, Jeez.

26:20.769 --> 26:21.997
Donna.

26:22.070 --> 26:23.038
Ronnie.

26:23.105 --> 26:25.198
Will you dance with me?

26:26.375 --> 26:28.343
Oh, yes.

26:28.410 --> 26:30.002
Yeah, sure.

26:46.764 --> 26:50.461
♪ Moon River ♪

26:50.535 --> 26:53.902
♪ Wider than a mile ♪

26:53.971 --> 26:57.840
♪ I'm crossing you in style ♪

26:57.910 --> 27:01.812
♪ Someday ♪

27:01.880 --> 27:06.146
♪ Oh, dreammaker ♪

27:06.218 --> 27:09.882
♪ You heartbreaker ♪

27:09.989 --> 27:13.425
♪ Wherever you're goin' ♪

27:13.493 --> 27:17.896
♪ I'm goin' your way ♪

27:17.964 --> 27:22.061
♪ Two drifters ♪

27:22.136 --> 27:25.003
♪ Off to see the world ♪

27:25.072 --> 27:29.099
♪ There's such a lot of world ♪

27:29.176 --> 27:33.011
♪ To see ♪

27:33.081 --> 27:37.452
♪ We're after
the same... # ♪

27:37.552 --> 27:41.886
♪ We're after
the same... # ♪

27:56.607 --> 27:59.303
2-Alpha, 2-Alpha,
this is 6, over.

27:59.376 --> 28:00.968
6, 6,
2-Actual, over.

28:01.044 --> 28:03.308
2-Actual, this is 6.
That's a roger.

28:03.380 --> 28:05.177
You have beaucoup gooks.

28:05.249 --> 28:06.648
They're coming at you.

28:06.717 --> 28:08.515
Echo-1's
pushing them. Over.

28:08.586 --> 28:09.917
6, 6, 2-Actual.

28:09.988 --> 28:11.319
Sit Rep as follows...

28:11.389 --> 28:13.357
two set in on the beach.

28:13.424 --> 28:15.289
The tracks are moving this way.

28:15.360 --> 28:17.851
Sounds like
beaucoup gooks in there.

28:17.929 --> 28:20.398
I'm finally going to see one.

28:20.466 --> 28:22.331
Relax, you'll be all right.

28:22.401 --> 28:23.959
Where you from, Wilson?

28:24.069 --> 28:25.969
First Battalion,
Ninth Motor "T."

28:26.038 --> 28:28.973
The Sergeant Major said the grunts
needed replacements,

28:29.041 --> 28:32.273
so they took me out
of battalion supply.

28:32.345 --> 28:34.745
Where are you from in the world?

28:34.814 --> 28:36.247
Oh, Venus, Georgia.

28:36.316 --> 28:37.977
This is my second tour.

28:38.051 --> 28:41.020
I haven't seen a Georgia boy
get hurt yet.

28:41.087 --> 28:42.486
You'll be all right.

28:42.555 --> 28:45.286
Echo-6, Echo-6,
Snake 1-9er...

28:46.928 --> 28:48.156
All right.

28:48.229 --> 28:51.323
Echo-1's taking incoming
northwest edge of the ville.

28:52.300 --> 28:54.825
We got gooks moving this way.

28:54.936 --> 28:56.370
Look out there, Sergeant.

28:56.438 --> 28:57.871
Can you see them?

28:57.940 --> 28:59.703
Right there.
You see them?

28:59.775 --> 29:01.538
They got rifles.

29:01.610 --> 29:03.544
Can you see the rifles?

29:03.612 --> 29:05.375
Right there.
You see them?

29:05.447 --> 29:06.881
You see them?

29:06.950 --> 29:08.611
Can you see the rifles?

29:08.685 --> 29:11.586
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

29:11.654 --> 29:13.053
Pass the word.

29:13.122 --> 29:14.749
When I give the order,

29:14.824 --> 29:16.553
I want to light up this ville

29:16.626 --> 29:18.059
like a motherfucking
Christmas tree.

29:18.127 --> 29:20.824
This time I think we got them!
Move out.

29:20.898 --> 29:23.298
Pass the word!
Fire on command!

29:23.400 --> 29:24.458
Wilson, come with me.

29:24.568 --> 29:25.796
Cover that big hooch!

29:25.903 --> 29:28.337
Fire on my command!
Pass the word!

29:28.405 --> 29:30.840
Corporal, start ranking.
Fire on my command!

29:30.909 --> 29:32.342
Fire on my command!

29:33.812 --> 29:34.779
Cease-fire!

29:34.846 --> 29:36.040
What happened?

29:36.114 --> 29:39.083
What the fuck are you doing?

29:42.154 --> 29:43.883
Cease-fire!

29:43.956 --> 29:45.355
What happened?

29:46.392 --> 29:47.359
Cease-fire!

29:47.426 --> 29:49.894
I want to know what happened!

29:49.962 --> 29:51.190
I don't know, sir.

29:51.263 --> 29:52.573
Possible accidental
discharge, sir.

29:52.598 --> 29:54.897
We better get
a sweep team in there.

29:54.968 --> 29:57.903
Take five men.
Tell me how many we got.

29:57.971 --> 29:58.903
Yes, sir.

29:58.972 --> 30:00.337
Motherfucker!

30:00.407 --> 30:02.307
Baldy on me!

30:02.376 --> 30:04.742
Brooks!
Martinez! On me!

30:04.811 --> 30:06.245
Wilson!
Wilson, on me!

30:06.314 --> 30:09.249
2-alpha, moving on the ville
at this time. Over.

30:09.317 --> 30:10.909
Line! Line! Line!

30:13.321 --> 30:15.221
Ironhand for fire mission.

30:15.289 --> 30:16.756
Stand by.

30:16.824 --> 30:21.660
Grid... 1-5-6-3-7-9er.

30:21.730 --> 30:23.163
Direction... 5-800.

30:23.232 --> 30:25.700
Gooks in the ville, Battery 6.

30:25.768 --> 30:27.167
Victor, Tango in effect.

30:27.269 --> 30:28.702
How copy? Over.

30:28.771 --> 30:29.704
Baldy! Baldy!

30:29.773 --> 30:31.741
Lai dai! Lai dai!

30:31.808 --> 30:34.208
Get him out!
Get him out!

30:34.277 --> 30:36.211
Come on, Baldy, come on.

30:36.279 --> 30:38.713
Check it out over there!
Everything out!

30:38.782 --> 30:40.215
Baldy, get everything out!

30:40.283 --> 30:42.252
Baldy! There!
Check it out!

30:42.319 --> 30:43.547
Echo-2, Alpha.

30:43.621 --> 30:46.055
Echo-2,
send your Sit Rep. Over.

30:46.123 --> 30:47.852
Lai dai! Lai dai!

30:47.925 --> 30:49.256
Lai dai! Lai dai!

30:49.326 --> 30:50.554
Get him out!

30:50.628 --> 30:51.890
Get him out!

30:51.962 --> 30:54.261
Check those hooches
and clear ASAP.

30:54.332 --> 30:57.062
We've got a fire mission
inbound. Over.

30:57.969 --> 31:00.233
Oh, my God.

31:00.338 --> 31:03.774
We didn't do this, did we?

31:03.842 --> 31:05.276
Oh, my God.

31:05.344 --> 31:06.777
Jesus Christ.

31:06.846 --> 31:08.040
Oh, my God.

31:10.917 --> 31:14.114
2-Actual-2, better get down
here quick,

31:14.187 --> 31:15.950
and bring the corpsmen.

31:16.023 --> 31:19.322
We got beaucoup wounded.
Civilians.

31:19.393 --> 31:21.725
Martinez, help me!

31:24.798 --> 31:26.629
We wasted them.

31:26.700 --> 31:30.330
Motherfucker!
We wasted them!

31:31.673 --> 31:33.163
Oh!

31:43.652 --> 31:45.051
Destroy.

31:45.121 --> 31:46.679
Where are the rifles?

31:47.790 --> 31:49.189
Where are the rifles?

31:49.258 --> 31:51.158
There ain't no fucking rifles.

31:51.228 --> 31:52.559
Damn it.

31:52.629 --> 31:54.096
Jesus fucking Christ!

31:54.164 --> 31:55.563
Well, help him then!

31:55.632 --> 31:58.100
Help him!
Help him! Help him!

31:58.168 --> 32:00.227
Oh, motherfuck...

32:01.171 --> 32:03.572
I want you to help him.

32:03.641 --> 32:04.573
Forgive us.

32:04.642 --> 32:06.974
Help me!
Somebody help me!

32:10.047 --> 32:11.480
6, 6, 2-Actual.

32:11.549 --> 32:13.073
Request emergency medevac.

32:13.184 --> 32:15.949
We got a lot
of friendly wounded. Over.

32:16.021 --> 32:17.283
Get out of there!

32:17.356 --> 32:19.790
Leave those wounded!
You got Arty inbound!

32:19.858 --> 32:21.052
Get out! Get out!

32:21.126 --> 32:23.287
Get back to the dunes!

32:23.362 --> 32:26.160
We got gooks
in the ville! Move out!

32:26.231 --> 32:27.961
Get out! Move out!

32:28.034 --> 32:29.296
That's a direct order!

32:29.369 --> 32:31.360
I want you out that door!

32:31.437 --> 32:33.598
It wasn't your fault,
goddamn it!

32:33.673 --> 32:36.574
They got in the goddamned way!

32:36.643 --> 32:38.076
Get off the deck!

32:38.144 --> 32:40.670
We got gooks in the ville!

32:40.781 --> 32:42.373
The baby!

32:42.483 --> 32:44.075
Get back to the dune!

32:44.185 --> 32:45.117
The baby!

32:45.186 --> 32:46.619
No! Move out!
Let's move!

32:46.687 --> 32:48.655
Kovic, move!

32:48.756 --> 32:50.054
Move out!

32:50.125 --> 32:51.592
Move out!
Move! Move!

32:51.660 --> 32:55.721
The ville is going to blow!

33:10.546 --> 33:11.774
Aah!

33:18.255 --> 33:21.588
Red! Abbot!

33:37.476 --> 33:41.537
Aah!

33:49.422 --> 33:51.083
Wilson!

33:51.191 --> 33:52.522
Wilson's hit!

34:34.637 --> 34:36.799
What happened?

34:36.873 --> 34:38.306
Where's First Platoon?

34:38.375 --> 34:40.239
For God's sake, Corpsman!

34:43.447 --> 34:45.312
Where's my "A" gunner?

35:15.182 --> 35:17.742
Sergeant Kovic
here to see you, sir.

35:17.818 --> 35:19.410
Stand easy, sergeant.

35:21.121 --> 35:23.215
Yeah, Kovic,
the lieutenant told me

35:23.291 --> 35:25.486
that was a pretty rough time.

35:25.560 --> 35:27.824
Yes, sir.
It was pretty bad.

35:27.929 --> 35:29.954
Ran into a few of them?

35:30.064 --> 35:31.224
Yes, sir.

35:32.367 --> 35:35.337
You want to see me
about something, Sergeant?

35:35.437 --> 35:36.563
Yes, sir.

35:36.638 --> 35:39.573
Like I said to the captain,
uh, sir...

35:39.641 --> 35:42.576
it was a very confusing day.

35:42.644 --> 35:43.770
The villagers...

35:43.846 --> 35:46.748
Yeah. I know about
the villagers, Sergeant.

35:46.816 --> 35:48.249
They...
the villagers...

35:48.318 --> 35:50.252
It was very, very unfortunate.

35:50.320 --> 35:52.652
The enemy used
the villagers as cover.

35:52.722 --> 35:53.814
Yes, sir.

35:54.924 --> 35:57.188
They popped up, started firing.

35:57.260 --> 35:59.058
We were running back, sir.

35:59.130 --> 36:00.597
It was real glary.

36:00.698 --> 36:02.097
Very confusing,

36:02.199 --> 36:04.793
and that's when
it happened, sir.

36:04.902 --> 36:06.130
What happened?

36:06.237 --> 36:09.138
Sir, that was when
Wilson was killed, sir.

36:09.206 --> 36:11.471
Yeah, I know about Wilson.

36:11.543 --> 36:13.135
Sir, see...

36:13.211 --> 36:15.645
he was the last one out,

36:15.714 --> 36:18.148
and that's when
it happened, sir.

36:18.216 --> 36:20.184
Sir, I think I might...

36:20.252 --> 36:22.653
I might have killed him, sir.

36:22.722 --> 36:24.121
I don't think so.

36:24.190 --> 36:26.590
He was coming up over the dune.

36:26.659 --> 36:29.287
I think I might have killed him.

36:29.362 --> 36:30.454
It's hard.

36:30.530 --> 36:33.193
I was out a couple of weeks ago.

36:33.267 --> 36:36.395
